omas, called Didymus’ (John 11:16; 20:24). <i>Didymos</i> is the Greek word for ‘twin’, and the name is the Greek form of an Aramaic byname meaning ‘twin’. The given name has always been popular throughout Christendom, in part because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":30,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":0}],"lifeSummary":"Thomas Goodale was born in 1425, in England. He had at least 1 son with Am Miller. He died in 1499, at the age of 74."},"et":{"1425–1499":"1425–1499","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1450–1539":"1450–1539","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Downham, Norfolk, England":"Downham West, Norfolk, England","England":"England"},"fi":{"1425–1499":"1425–1499","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1450–1539":"1450–1539","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Downham, Norfolk, England":"Downham West, Norfolk, England","England":"England"},"fr":{"1425–1499":"1425–1499","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1450–1539":"1450–1539","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1455":"1455","1450":"1450","1539":"1539","1504":"1504","Downham, Norfolk, England":"Downham West, Norfolk, Angleterre","England":"Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Thomas Goodale est né en 1425, à Angleterre. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Am Miller. Il est décédé en 1499, à l’âge de 74 ans."},"de":{"1425–1499":"1425–1499","1425–1504":"1425–1504","1450–1539":"1450–1539","1425":"1425","1499":"1499","1455":"1455","1